Title 
Design and Execution of an Email Marketing Campaign Using Mailchimp (Free 
Plan) 



Aim 
To design, execute, and analyze an email marketing campaign for a fictional product 
or service using Mailchimp’s free features, including audience creation, contact 
management, email design, scheduling, and performance tracking. 
Objectives 
1.
 
To understand the fundamentals of email marketing and permission-based 
communication 
2.
 
To create and configure a Mailchimp account using the free plan 
3.
 
To build and manage an email audience 
4.
 
To import and organize contacts using tags and segments 
5.
 
To design and send a regular email campaign 
6.
 
To analyze campaign performance using basic analytics 




Theory 
Introduction to Email Marketing 
Email marketing is a direct digital communication channel used to share information, 
promotions, updates, and content with a targeted audience. Unlike social media, email 
marketing allows organizations to communicate directly with users who have explicitly 
given permission to receive messages. 


Effective email marketing : 
● 
Builds long-term relationships 
● 
Drives repeat engagement 
● 
Supports personalization and segmentation 
● 
Provides measurable performance metrics 
Mailchimp as an Email Marketing Platform 
Mailchimp is a web-based email marketing platform that enables users to create, 
send, and analyze email campaigns. Its free plan supports: 
● 
Up to 250 contacts
 
● 
Up to 500 email sends per month
 
● 
Regular email campaigns 
● 
Basic audience segmentation 
● 
Open and click tracking 
Mailchimp enforces strict anti-spam and consent policies, making ethical email 
practices mandatory.






Result 
An email marketing campaign was successfully designed and executed using 
Mailchimp’s free plan. Contacts were managed ethically, emails were sent to targeted 
segments, and campaign performance was measured using open and click tracking. 
